The Legacy of the Arte della Seta - Gold Colored Fox|https://goldcoloredfox.com/2021/02/09/the-legacy-of-the-arte-della-seta/|With that out of my system — onward to Florence!  ## Ospedale degli Innocenti In 1419, the Arte della Seta (the Florence Silk Guild), one of the wealthiest in the city and thus driven to philanthropy, commissioned Filippo Brunelleschi to design the Ospedale degli Innocenti. While Ospedale translates literally as “hospital,” the structure’s purpose was that of an orphanage. The building is now a museum (it opened about six months after my visit) holding works by Luca della Robbia, Sandro Botticelli, and Domenico Ghirlandaio. This was Brunelleschi’s first architectural commission (he had previously completed sculptural work for the Florence  ...    What you see at the far end here is the admissions window for the Ospedale
